@startuml Contract Generator Flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor transparent

title **ContractorPro - Contract Generator Workflow**

actor Contractor
database System
participant "Job Setup" as JOB
participant "Location Builder" as LOC
participant "Task Templates" as TEMP
participant "Contract Engine" as CONTRACT

== Initial Job Creation ==
Contractor -> JOB : Create Job\n(Client details, project type, scope)
JOB -> System : Store project info

== Location Breakdown ==
Contractor -> LOC : Add Locations\n(Kitchen, Bathroom, Bedroom, etc.)
LOC -> System : Store room-by-room breakdown
note right of LOC : Each location has:\n• Name & description\n• Square footage\n• Order for contract

== Task Assignment ==
loop For Each Location
  Contractor -> TEMP : Select Task Templates\n(Demolition, Installation, Finishing)
  TEMP -> LOC : Apply pre-written tasks\nwith estimated costs
end
note right of TEMP : Templates include:\n• Task descriptions\n• Default costs\n• Time estimates

== Contract Generation ==
Contractor -> CONTRACT : Generate Contract
CONTRACT -> JOB : Pull client details
CONTRACT -> LOC : Pull all locations
CONTRACT -> TEMP : Pull all assigned tasks
CONTRACT -> CONTRACT : Calculate total value\nfrom included tasks

CONTRACT -> Contractor : **Professional Contract Document**\n• Auto-generated contract number\n• Client information pre-filled\n• Location-by-location breakdown\n• Task details with costs\n• Terms & conditions\n• Total project value

note right of CONTRACT
**Auto-Generated Contract:**
• CON-20250103-A1B2C3
• "Kitchen Remodel - John Smith"
• Room-by-room scope
• Professional formatting
• Ready for client signature
end note

@enduml